               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470104-name-195" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470104-name-195" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470104-name-195" type="surname" value="HARROD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470104-name-195" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM HARROD.</persName>
                  </hi> I am a butter and cheeseman—I live in Berkshire. On the 30th of Dec., about eight o'clock in the evening, I was coming to Brentford with a cart—I had a basket containing the lard and honey and other things stated, and two dead turkeys were in the cart—this is the basket.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470104-name-196" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470104-name-196" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470104-name-196" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470104-name-196" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>CHARLES SMITH.</persName>
                  </hi> I am a gardener, and live at Isleworth. About eight o'clock that night I came out of Mr. Durham's, where Mr. Harrod was doing</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184701040023"></xptr>
               <p>a little business—I saw the prisoner take a turkey from the cart—I went and told Mr. Harrod of it—I am sure I saw it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. BALDWIN.</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Do you mean to swear it was the prisoner? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—I knew the prisoner well when I saw him take it, but I did not know his name.</p>
